React To-Do App

Description:
This is a simple React application to manage a to-do list. Users can add new tasks, mark tasks as complete, edit tasks, and delete tasks. The application uses React functional components and hooks for state management.

Features:
- Add new tasks
- Mark tasks as completed
- Edit existing tasks
- Delete tasks
- Persist tasks using local storage (optional)

Installation:
1. Make sure Node.js and npm are installed.
2. Clone the repository.
3. Navigate to the project folder.
4. Run 'npm install' to install dependencies.
5. Run 'npm start' to launch the app in development mode.

File Structure:
- package.json          : Project dependencies and scripts
- package-lock.json     : Lockfile for npm dependencies
- angular.json          : Angular config (if migrated from Angular project)
- tsconfig.json         : TypeScript configuration
- index.html            : Main HTML file
- main.ts / main.jsx    : Entry point for React app
- styles.css / app.css  : CSS styles
- app.ts / app.jsx      : Main App component
- app.spec.ts           : Test file (if applicable)
- app.routes.ts         : Route definitions
- app.config.ts         : App configuration

Usage:
- Open the app in the browser at http://localhost:3000
- Use the interface to manage your to-do list

